      "FacilityID": 52064,
      "SummaryText": "Sorbent Technology stores 2500 gals of Liquid Bromine which is then slowly evaporated through an external heat exchanger to gas phase bromine. This gas phase bromine is then absorbed into various substrates through a contacting/mixing process. The finish product is a dry, chemically stable powder used in the power generation industry to remove air pollutants. A complete safety and containment system is in place for the active bromine portions of the system. All areas were reactive liquid or vapor bromine are present have complete vapor/liquid isolation capability. Each area has water blanketing capacity, and vapor isolation with neutralization capacity thru a packed scrubber tower.  All bromine areas are automatically alarmed and the scrubber has power back up for the system. Employees are given extensive emergency training on proceedures for safely responding to all loss of containment and other accidents."
    }
